page.html:
"Just the basic facts"
I'm from Guitar Hero. More or less I played it for 6 years, the Xbox360 version, (and yes, with the guitar controller).Embarassing Before it I played a pc game called Frets on Fire, it was basically a transposition of Guitar Hero for the pc, so that's actually where I learned what VSRG are. When I stoped being a console gamer I didnt' know there were others VSRG, but my brother made me discover a game called Guitar Flash, so I just played it for 3 years, it's still same thing of the above mentioned games. All these games hadn't any community and it was boring to play them alone, however I posted a gameplay of Guitar Glash on my YouTube channel (it has only that video it's not even worth to look at it), and a friend of mine watched it, then he told me that I had to play osu!mania. Let me digress, I already tried osu! 3 years before that this guy told me to play it, but at that time, mania mode didn't exist, (or maybe it's just that I didn't know it) and I only played the standard mode, that I didn't enjoy. Anyway I tried osu!mania and I found it quite interesting, especially becouse there is a large community, and I was used to play games without any community, so this was a new thing and it captured my interest, and also in osu! maps there are a lot of different patterns, instead in the other games I played they were always the same spammed in different ways in every map. That's all, I started by playing 7k, becouse a friend of mine told me that is better to start with 7k so it wouldn't have been hard to pass from 4k to 7k like for the most of people.

More or less I played it for 6 years, the Xbox360 version, (and yes, with the guitar controller).[spoiler]Embarassing[/spoiler] Before it I played a pc game called Frets on Fire, it was basically a transposition of Guitar Hero for the pc, so that's actually where I learned what VSRG are. When I stoped being a console gamer I didnt' know there were others VSRG, but my brother made me discover a game called Guitar Flash, so I just played it for 3 years, it's still same thing of the above mentioned games. All these games hadn't any community and it was boring to play them alone, however I posted a gameplay of Guitar Glash on my YouTube channel (it has only that video it's not even worth to look at it), and a friend of mine watched it, then he told me that I had to play osu!mania. Let me digress, I already tried osu! 3 years before that this guy told me to play it, but at that time, mania mode didn't exist, (or maybe it's just that I didn't know it) and I only played the standard mode, that I didn't enjoy. Anyway I tried osu!mania and I found it quite interesting, especially becouse there is a large community, and I was used to play games without any community, so this was a new thing and it captured my interest, and also in osu! maps there are a lot of different patterns, instead in the other games I played they were always the same spammed in different ways in every map.
